Class ScriptExecutionException

    @PublishedApi(value=ADDITIONS_ALLOWED)
 @PublishedApiDomain(value=AUTOMATION_IF)
public class ScriptExecutionException
extends ScriptingException
implements IDebugable
    ScriptExecutionException is the standard type thrown by an IScriptTask execution. The IScriptTask.call(com.vector.cfg.util.servicecontext.IServiceContext, Object...) method will throw a subclass of ScriptExecutionException to indicate failure of the execution.

    Every thrown exception from the script task client code is wrapped into an instance of ScriptExecutionException, before handed to the caller.

    The exception provides information of the:

    • Where
    • Stackframe
    • What went wrong
    • Which script
    • What script file

    A client code should use subtypes of ScriptClientExecutionException to implement own exception types with the same behavior, instead of subclassing the class directly.
